FBIS4-63155 "drsov098_r_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 Azerbaijan Democratic Congress Opposes Stationing Russian Troops Democratic Congress Opposes Stationing Russian Troops NC2005033294 Baku TURAN in English 1623 GMT 19 May 94 NC2005033294 Baku TURAN English BFN [Text] Baku, 19 May (TURAN)--The session of Azerbaijan's Democratic Congress completed last evening. The agenda included only one question -- return of Russian troops to Azerbaijan. The participants of the session unanimously adopted the resolution which condemns the activities of the current leadership of the republic aimed at "return of Russian troops to the country". The resolution reads that "if Russian troops be brought to Azerbaijan, the Democratic Congress reserves right to conduct rallies of protest." The Democratic Congress was founded on 23 March 1994. It includes five opposition parties: Musavat, the Popular Front, the Democratic Party, the Party of Nation's Liberty, and Ana Torpag Party.
